<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFGorham.2C_E.1991">Gorham, E. (1991). "Biogeochemistry: its origins and development". <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Biogeochemistry_(journal)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Biogeochemistry (journal) (page does not exist)">Biogeochemistry</a></i> <b>13</b> (3): 199–239. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2FBF00002942" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2FBF00002942" rel="nofollow">10.1007/BF00002942</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Biogeochemistry%3A+its+origins+and+development&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BBiogeochemistry+%28journal%29%7CBiogeochemistry%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Gorham%2C+E.&amp;rft.au=Gorham%2C+E.&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.volume=13&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=199%E2%80%93239&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1007%2FBF00002942&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gaia_hypothesis"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFKarhu.2C_J.A.Holland.2C_H.D.">Karhu, J.A.; Holland, H.D. (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1996-10-01"><a href="/wiki/1996" title="1996">1996</a>-<a href="/wiki/October_1" title="October 1">10-01</a></span>). "<a href="http://geology.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/content/abstract/24/10/867" class="external text" title="http://geology.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/content/abstract/24/10/867" rel="nofollow">Carbon isotopes and the rise of atmospheric oxygen</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/Geology_(journal)" title="Geology (journal)">Geology</a></i> <b>24</b> (10): 867–870. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1130%2F0091-7613%281996%29024%3C0867%3ACIATRO%3E2.3.CO%3B2" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1130%2F0091-7613%281996%29024%3C0867%3ACIATRO%3E2.3.CO%3B2" rel="nofollow">10.1130/0091-7613(1996)024&lt;0867:CIATRO&gt;2.3.CO;2</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://geology.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/content/abstract/24/10/867" class="external free" title="http://geology.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/content/abstract/24/10/867" rel="nofollow">http://geology.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/content/abstract/24/10/867</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Carbon+isotopes+and+the+rise+of+atmospheric+oxygen&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BGeology+%28journal%29%7CGeology%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Karhu%2C+J.A.&amp;rft.au=Karhu%2C+J.A.&amp;rft.au=Holland%2C+H.D.&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B1996-10-01%5D%5D&amp;rft.volume=24&amp;rft.issue=10&amp;rft.pages=867%E2%80%93870&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1130%2F0091-7613%281996%29024%3C0867%3ACIATRO%3E2.3.CO%3B2&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fgeology.geoscienceworld.org%2Fcgi%2Fcontent%2Fabstract%2F24%2F10%2F867&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.